<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-04-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-04-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="64" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d64">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 23700/17.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Ambassador <persName type="from">Hill</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Extract.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Berlin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-04-22"><hi rend="italic">April 22,
                                1910</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Referring to department’s April 16, Ambassador Hill says formalities for
                            transit from Germany are the same as extradition from that country, and
                            that an agent can not accompany fugitive on board German vessel or
                            through Germany.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>